506
00:35:31,295 --> 00:35:34,355
...so that we can focus...

507
00:35:35,766 --> 00:35:38,462
...on what really matters.

508
00:36:16,607 --> 00:36:20,407
DOCTOR:
We lost him. I'm so sorry.

509
00:36:24,549 --> 00:36:30,545
X:
In time, darkness will give way.

510
00:36:32,890 --> 00:36:34,653
And then...

511
00:36:37,128 --> 00:36:39,119
...you must live.

512
00:36:39,497 --> 00:36:44,025
Live like you've never lived before.

513
00:36:46,737 --> 00:36:50,639
I was told that you're the guy
and for the money I'm paying you...

514
00:36:50,808 --> 00:36:52,867
...you better be the guy.

515
00:36:54,378 --> 00:36:57,040
Trevor, what can I do
to make a miracle happen for you?

516
00:36:57,515 --> 00:37:01,542
I was going through his stuff,
I found this raw footage.

517
00:37:02,119 --> 00:37:04,110
It's his last song.

518
00:37:04,288 --> 00:37:06,279
[GUITAR PLAYING ON VIDEO]

519
00:37:08,326 --> 00:37:11,090
[SINGING]
On and on

520
00:37:11,262 --> 00:37:13,162
On and on

521
00:37:13,998 --> 00:37:16,466
- Oh this is good.
TREVOR: Yeah, it's good.

522
00:37:16,634 --> 00:37:20,161
- This is really good.
- Make it a hit.

523
00:37:25,810 --> 00:37:28,176
I've wanted to tell you.

524
00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:31,772
What is the point of talking, huh?

525
00:37:31,949 --> 00:37:33,314
What is the point?

526
00:37:35,519 --> 00:37:38,147
Thirty-five years ago today...

527
00:37:38,522 --> 00:37:44,586
...my parents stood at the altar
of a tiny church in Mount Bethel, Texas.

528
00:37:49,333 --> 00:37:53,997
And it was there
that they heard these words.

529
00:37:54,805 --> 00:37:58,935
Love is patient, love is kind.

530
00:37:59,277 --> 00:38:01,177
Not jealous...

531
00:38:01,479 --> 00:38:05,472
...or boastful or rude.

532
00:38:08,152 --> 00:38:10,347
So you're fighting.

533
00:38:14,025 --> 00:38:16,425
It's not what is said.

534
00:38:18,529 --> 00:38:19,791
It's what's not.

535
00:38:19,964 --> 00:38:21,693
I'm curious.

536
00:38:21,866 --> 00:38:28,066
How could she say anything
that would change her past?

537
00:38:30,941 --> 00:38:32,568
She can't.

538
00:38:33,744 --> 00:38:36,542
It does not demand its own way.

539
00:38:36,747 --> 00:38:38,612
It's not irritable.

540
00:38:39,083 --> 00:38:42,883
And it keeps no record of being wrong.

541
00:38:45,923 --> 00:38:50,155
Although my sister Eva
never really saw it that way.

542
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:52,353
Some people are just easier to love
than others.

543
00:38:52,530 --> 00:38:54,293
[GUESTS LAUGHING]

544
00:38:54,465 --> 00:38:56,296
Fair enough. Fair enough. Fair enough.

545
00:38:56,467 --> 00:39:00,870
It does not rejoice in injustice...

546
00:39:01,038 --> 00:39:05,839
...but rejoices
whenever the truth wins out.

547
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:07,875
Love never gives up.

548
00:39:08,045 --> 00:39:10,343
It never loses faith.

549
00:39:10,681 --> 00:39:12,911
It's always hopeful.

550
00:39:13,284 --> 00:39:18,722
And it endures every circumstance.

551
00:39:21,492 --> 00:39:24,017
You did it, Mom and Dad. You lived it.

552
00:39:24,195 --> 00:39:25,492
Every word.

553
00:39:25,663 --> 00:39:27,790
Congratulations. I love you both.

554
00:39:27,965 --> 00:39:30,661
MAN: Hear, hear.
- I love you, son.

555
00:39:35,773 --> 00:39:37,764
[JAzz MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

556
00:39:40,578 --> 00:39:45,982
You've been staring at her all night.
And you haven't said a word.

557
00:39:46,150 --> 00:39:50,109
Evie, you wouldn't understand.

558
00:39:50,287 --> 00:39:52,619
Aaron, I'm divorced.

559
00:39:53,157 --> 00:39:55,921
Believe me, I'll understand.

560
00:39:56,794 --> 00:39:58,591
Not this time.

561
00:40:01,832 --> 00:40:04,801
My one regret...

562
00:40:05,770 --> 00:40:10,798
...is that I didn't give Scott
another chance.

563
00:40:12,843 --> 00:40:17,007
You know, he hurt me, and I was done.

564
00:40:17,181 --> 00:40:18,580
That was it.

565
00:40:18,749 --> 00:40:20,341
He deserved it.

566
00:40:22,219 --> 00:40:23,743
Maybe...

567
00:40:26,791 --> 00:40:30,352
...but I'll never get
a 35th wedding anniversary, will I?

568
00:40:31,362 --> 00:40:36,994
X: What would your father do
if he were in your shoes with your mother?

569
00:40:38,436 --> 00:40:40,267
Alice is not my mother.

570
00:40:40,438 --> 00:40:42,269
No...

571
00:40:43,073 --> 00:40:48,511
...but your mother's been wrong
and your father forgave her.

572
00:40:48,679 --> 00:40:50,806
This is different.

573
00:40:50,981 --> 00:40:53,973
How? Because it's you?

574
00:40:56,954 --> 00:41:00,287
Some people don't have
the freedom to forgive.

575
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:03,655
Freedom? So you're a slave?

576
00:41:04,061 --> 00:41:05,892
I have a duty to the public I serve.

577
00:41:06,063 --> 00:41:07,325
Right.

578
00:41:07,498 --> 00:41:10,092
The politician. The lawyer.

579
00:41:10,267 --> 00:41:12,963
You can't love by the letter of the law.

580
00:41:13,137 --> 00:41:15,264
Are you a good man?

581
00:41:15,439 --> 00:41:17,430
[KATHERINE McPHEE'S "SAY GOODBYE"
PLAYING]

582
00:41:20,511 --> 00:41:22,308
I think so.

583
00:41:23,147 --> 00:41:26,048
Are you a compassionate man?

584
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,010
Yes.

585
00:41:32,723 --> 00:41:35,954
Words are like scissors

586
00:41:40,030 --> 00:41:41,861
I'm sorry.

587
00:41:46,270 --> 00:41:47,760
No.

588
00:41:51,208 --> 00:41:53,699
X: Do you love her?
AARON: Yes.

589
00:41:55,212 --> 00:41:57,339
Then know this.

590
00:41:57,681 --> 00:42:00,809
People are not perfect...

591
00:42:03,354 --> 00:42:05,049
...but love is.

592
00:42:05,222 --> 00:42:08,589
When we say goodbye

593
00:42:15,032 --> 00:42:16,624
X:
What is it about this doctor...

594
00:42:17,301 --> 00:42:21,431
...that makes him
so deserving of justice?

595
00:42:21,972 --> 00:42:23,963
He's a killer.

596
00:42:26,143 --> 00:42:28,407
So you're going to arrest him?

597
00:42:29,647 --> 00:42:30,807
That's right.

598
00:42:32,583 --> 00:42:35,017
And if he resists?

599
00:42:36,287 --> 00:42:38,847
- You'll kill him?
- Without hesitation.

600
00:42:40,424 --> 00:42:41,686
X:
What then?

601
00:42:41,859 --> 00:42:45,727
JAKE: Right down the line,
I'll get all the criminals that deserve it.

602
00:42:52,236 --> 00:42:55,933
X:
Judge, jury and executioner.

603
00:42:56,106 --> 00:42:57,937
All in one.

604
00:42:58,142 --> 00:43:00,576
So what if the brother gets the money?

605
00:43:00,844 --> 00:43:04,109
Their father shouldn't have cut him
out of the will in the first place.

606
00:43:05,482 --> 00:43:09,919
This whole mess
has gotten way too dirty.

607
00:43:10,387 --> 00:43:12,082
I say...

608
00:43:12,756 --> 00:43:14,690
...we wash our hands of it...

609
00:43:14,858 --> 00:43:16,655
...and move on to real criminals.

610
00:43:18,228 --> 00:43:20,162
I can't do that.

611
00:43:20,731 --> 00:43:22,892
No, you can't, can you?

612
00:43:24,335 --> 00:43:25,529
And why is that?

613
00:43:27,938 --> 00:43:30,099
They think that they're entitled.

614
00:43:30,274 --> 00:43:31,901
Entitled?

615
00:43:34,044 --> 00:43:37,172
Or is it that you believe...

616
00:43:38,949 --> 00:43:41,349
...that Ortus...

617
00:43:42,453 --> 00:43:44,318
...killed your wife?

618
00:43:44,922 --> 00:43:46,822
Oh, come on, Jake.

619
00:43:46,991 --> 00:43:50,586
How can I send detectives in the field
if I don't know everything about them?

620
00:43:54,598 --> 00:43:56,896
She was in grad school.

621
00:43:57,167 --> 00:44:00,898
She was offered a thousand dollars
to participate in an experiment...

622
00:44:01,071 --> 00:44:04,268
...with doctor Richard Ortus.

623
00:44:05,309 --> 00:44:09,609
He told her that it was an experiment
in cryogenic anesthesia...

624
00:44:09,813 --> 00:44:13,681
...using the freezing of tissue
to assist in surgery.

625
00:44:15,919 --> 00:44:20,015
He said they just freeze a little bit
of her arm and bring her right back.

626
00:44:21,859 --> 00:44:23,053
Easy money.

627
00:44:25,996 --> 00:44:30,729
She said we could never afford
to have a honeymoon...

628
00:44:31,335 --> 00:44:33,428
...and now we can.

629
00:44:35,773 --> 00:44:38,207
And I never saw her again.

630
00:44:39,710 --> 00:44:41,439
I'm sorry.

631
00:44:43,347 --> 00:44:47,443
He covered his tracks,
but I know he killed her.

632
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:52,785
When setting out on revenge...

633
00:44:52,956 --> 00:44:56,050
...one must first dig two graves.

634
00:44:57,161 --> 00:45:00,096
One for the victim...

635
00:45:01,231 --> 00:45:04,359
...but the other is for your heart.

636
00:45:12,209 --> 00:45:16,305
All that brilliance inside of your head...

637
00:45:17,247 --> 00:45:20,478
...and you still haven't figured it out.

638
00:45:21,351 --> 00:45:23,512
Or maybe you do now.

639
00:45:24,421 --> 00:45:26,389
That's it, isn't it?

640
00:45:26,757 --> 00:45:30,249
That deep churn in your soul.

641
00:45:30,661 --> 00:45:33,255
You know you have a choice to make.

642
00:45:34,031 --> 00:45:35,896
It's you...

643
00:45:36,467 --> 00:45:38,298
...or it's me.

644
00:45:39,403 --> 00:45:45,205
If you want them to leave you alone,
the money has to stop from flowing.

645
00:45:48,946 --> 00:45:52,143
You're going to have to kill me.

646
00:46:06,964 --> 00:46:08,829
Look at me.

647
00:46:11,401 --> 00:46:13,335
I'm miserable.

648
00:46:19,510 --> 00:46:21,978
End my suffering.

649
00:46:28,452 --> 00:46:30,750
Set yourself free.

650
00:46:44,101 --> 00:46:46,092
[MACHINERY CLICKING AND WHIRRING]

651
00:46:52,409 --> 00:46:53,842
No.

652
00:47:00,484 --> 00:47:01,974
Let's do it.

653
00:47:02,519 --> 00:47:04,510
[SANDFROG'S "FACEDOWN" PLAYING]

654
00:47:11,361 --> 00:47:15,297
Don't get you up so we cave in

655
00:47:15,465 --> 00:47:19,595
You act like you never feared someone

656
00:47:20,270 --> 00:47:24,536
And we'll give up, so wasted

657
00:47:24,708 --> 00:47:29,771
You think you know
The answers for everyone

658
00:47:32,583 --> 00:47:36,952
So breathe another day

659
00:47:37,120 --> 00:47:41,113
To see another way

660
00:47:41,859 --> 00:47:47,058
Convince me there's a reason
To prove to you

661
00:47:47,231 --> 00:47:49,222
Dr. Richard Ortus!

662
00:47:49,399 --> 00:47:51,731
We have a warrant to search your boat.

663
00:48:14,625 --> 00:48:16,456
JAKE:
He's dead.

664
00:48:17,527 --> 00:48:19,256
X:
What now?

665
00:48:20,430 --> 00:48:22,193
JAKE:
I don't know.

666
00:48:23,667 --> 00:48:27,660
Where are you running to?

667
00:48:30,007 --> 00:48:32,498
Did you think I...?

668
00:48:32,676 --> 00:48:34,906
X: How do you feel
when I mention Spenser's name?

669
00:48:35,078 --> 00:48:38,206
ALICE: Spenser is in the past.
X: To a certain degree?

670
00:48:38,382 --> 00:48:41,510
ALICE: I understand now that he had his life
and I had to get mine.

671
00:48:41,685 --> 00:48:46,281
In order to begin something,
you have to end something.

672
00:48:46,456 --> 00:48:48,754
I swear to you, I've done that.

673
00:48:48,926 --> 00:48:51,520
No, there is unfinished business.

674
00:48:52,029 --> 00:48:54,657
I think you're ready for a face-to-face.

675
00:48:55,365 --> 00:48:56,764
No.

676
00:48:57,301 --> 00:48:59,769
No, I don't ever
wanna have to see him again.

677
00:48:59,937 --> 00:49:01,632
Not him.

678
00:49:02,339 --> 00:49:03,363
Her.

679
00:49:03,540 --> 00:49:05,804
- Why don't we get going, okay? Okay.
- Okay.

680
00:49:09,880 --> 00:49:12,542
ALICE:
There's nothing I can say to her.

681
00:49:13,083 --> 00:49:14,710
X:
Who is your future?

682
00:49:14,885 --> 00:49:16,443
ALICE:
I want it to be Aaron.

683
00:49:16,620 --> 00:49:17,678
X:
And who is your past?

684
00:49:17,854 --> 00:49:19,549
ALICE: Spenser.
X: Okay.

685
00:49:20,123 --> 00:49:23,354
You can't have a future
until you've buried the past.

686
00:49:23,527 --> 00:49:25,552
I have done that.

687
00:49:25,729 --> 00:49:29,028
What began
as one man and one woman...

688
00:49:29,499 --> 00:49:34,493
...has become a wave
throughout this entire city.

689
00:49:34,771 --> 00:49:38,537
A jilted wife turned cold,
an isolated daughter.

690
00:49:39,176 --> 00:49:43,875
A boyfriend discovers a past
that hurts him so deeply...

691
00:49:44,815 --> 00:49:47,909
...he seeks comfort in his power.

692
00:49:48,986 --> 00:49:50,578
What do you want me to do?

693
00:49:50,754 --> 00:49:53,245
If you want peace...

694
00:49:54,725 --> 00:49:56,886
...you have to make it.

695
00:50:07,637 --> 00:50:10,197
ALICE:
Two years ago I had cancer.

696
00:50:11,675 --> 00:50:13,609
Alice Bordeaux.

697
00:50:13,877 --> 00:50:16,107
ALICE:
Spenser was my doctor.

698
00:50:16,546 --> 00:50:23,213
Won't you turn your eyes?

699
00:50:26,990 --> 00:50:28,821
ALICE:
He was there for me.

700
00:50:30,927 --> 00:50:33,953
Since when do you see your doctor
at lunch?

701
00:50:34,364 --> 00:50:36,059
What's going on?

702
00:50:36,366 --> 00:50:39,267
He was there every step of the way.

703
00:50:40,303 --> 00:50:42,328
You're cancer-free.

704
00:50:42,539 --> 00:50:46,236
In that moment, he wasn't just a man.

705
00:50:47,911 --> 00:50:49,708
You did it.

706
00:50:50,313 --> 00:50:52,577
He certainly wasn't a married man.

707
00:50:52,749 --> 00:50:54,182
He was my hero.

708
00:50:54,351 --> 00:50:57,115
A man who saved my life.

709
00:51:00,290 --> 00:51:03,020
It wasn't about taking away what he had.

710
00:51:03,193 --> 00:51:06,390
It was about having a piece of this man
all to myself...

711
00:51:06,563 --> 00:51:08,895
...if only for a moment.

712
00:51:09,199 --> 00:51:10,894
I don't know what to say.

713
00:51:11,635 --> 00:51:13,569
Things got out of control.

714
00:51:13,737 --> 00:51:17,173
But suddenly, it all stopped.

715
00:51:17,474 --> 00:51:20,034
Do I have to tell her everything?

716
00:51:20,310 --> 00:51:22,505
X:
What does she deserve?

717
00:51:22,779 --> 00:51:24,610
Everything.

718
00:51:31,388 --> 00:51:33,117
X:
How do you feel?

719
00:51:35,392 --> 00:51:36,791
Hollow.

720
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:38,894
We always feel empty...

721
00:51:39,062 --> 00:51:40,962
...when we've poured everything out.

722
00:51:41,631 --> 00:51:44,794
Sin is a word from archery.

723
00:51:44,968 --> 00:51:48,563
It means to miss the mark.

724
00:51:50,207 --> 00:51:53,142
We all miss. That's not the issue.

725
00:51:54,377 --> 00:51:56,208
What is?

726
00:51:56,446 --> 00:51:58,414
What we do with our next shot.

727
00:51:58,748 --> 00:52:00,739
Don't miss again.

728
00:52:02,552 --> 00:52:05,953
- She had an affair.
EVA: Before she met you.

729
00:52:06,289 --> 00:52:07,654
Can people not change?

730
00:52:08,558 --> 00:52:11,550
- I didn't say that.
- No, but you meant it.

731
00:52:11,728 --> 00:52:13,559
Because you're perfect...

732
00:52:13,730 --> 00:52:15,220
...right?

733
00:52:15,665 --> 00:52:16,859
And she's not?

734
00:52:17,567 --> 00:52:20,195
So she's gotta go.

735
00:52:20,437 --> 00:52:22,871
What do you want me to do, Evie?

736
00:52:24,107 --> 00:52:26,803
Give up every single thing I've ever had?

737
00:52:27,077 --> 00:52:29,011
Just to be with her. Some girl.

738
00:52:29,179 --> 00:52:32,148
If you love her, yes.

739
00:52:34,651 --> 00:52:36,141
Okay.

740
00:52:38,455 --> 00:52:39,547
Aaron...

741
00:52:39,723 --> 00:52:41,953
...when I married Scott...

742
00:52:42,626 --> 00:52:46,722
...I didn't marry a man,
I married a resume.

743
00:52:48,932 --> 00:52:50,490
And after 10 years...

744
00:52:51,201 --> 00:52:53,328
...and two kids...

745
00:52:55,038 --> 00:52:56,903
...a resume is not enough.

746
00:52:57,073 --> 00:53:01,703
You can't live someone else's life...

747
00:53:03,146 --> 00:53:07,082
...and chase after someone else's title.

748
00:53:10,153 --> 00:53:12,121
You've got to live your own.

749
00:53:18,094 --> 00:53:20,085
[JETSTREAM'S "HALFWAY TO HAPPINESS"
PLAYING]

750
00:53:28,271 --> 00:53:30,068
AARON:
Forty-fifteen.

751
00:53:33,543 --> 00:53:38,571
You can search a thousand hours
And never find out what to do

752
00:53:39,482 --> 00:53:42,007
It's a curse

753
00:53:42,185 --> 00:53:44,949
Which God has placed upon you

754
00:53:45,121 --> 00:53:50,286
The space of never knowing
If you'll ever be any good

755
00:53:51,995 --> 00:53:54,793
Maybe sometimes doing the right thing

756
00:53:56,066 --> 00:53:58,534
Isn't doing what feels good

757
00:54:00,103 --> 00:54:03,869
I'm feeling halfway

758
00:54:04,040 --> 00:54:05,530
Here we go.

759
00:54:07,277 --> 00:54:09,745
I'm feeling happiness

760
00:54:16,152 --> 00:54:17,983
Man, what's got into you today?

761
00:54:18,154 --> 00:54:20,850
- You are possessed.
AARON: Good play.

762
00:54:21,024 --> 00:54:24,653
Yeah. You're not much of a liar
for a politician, you know that?

763
00:54:24,828 --> 00:54:26,921
It's good to see you off that stool.

764
00:54:27,130 --> 00:54:28,495
Listen...

765
00:54:31,468 --> 00:54:33,493
...I don't know what to do about her.

766
00:54:34,838 --> 00:54:37,432
There are a lot of women out there.

767
00:54:37,607 --> 00:54:41,907
Last I checked, one DA. One.

768
00:54:43,947 --> 00:54:45,812
I know. I-

769
00:54:45,982 --> 00:54:49,179
- There's more-
- Hey. Hey. Listen to me.

770
00:54:49,352 --> 00:54:53,254
You've been waiting your whole life
for this moment.

771
00:54:55,292 --> 00:54:57,590
You don't need any more baggage.

772
00:54:58,295 --> 00:55:00,354
That's how you end up like me.

773
00:55:08,171 --> 00:55:10,469
ALICE:
What were you guys talking about?

774
00:55:14,544 --> 00:55:18,071
This song is amazing.

775
00:55:22,052 --> 00:55:26,216
Imagine the roar of the audience
when you play this song.

776
00:55:28,024 --> 00:55:30,356
Just before you finish your set...

777
00:55:30,527 --> 00:55:32,256
...you'll take to the piano...

778
00:55:32,429 --> 00:55:36,331
...and you'll tell a story
about young Will.

779
00:55:37,667 --> 00:55:41,125
This photograph will appear
in the background on the jumbo screen.

780
00:55:41,304 --> 00:55:42,794
And then...

781
00:55:43,807 --> 00:55:47,937
Then you will play the song that you wrote
in his memory.

782
00:55:48,278 --> 00:55:49,643
That's your big idea?

783
00:55:49,813 --> 00:55:52,338
You want me to steal my son's song.

784
00:55:52,515 --> 00:55:55,040
"Steal" is such a subjective word.

785
00:55:55,218 --> 00:55:58,244
I mean, a harsh, harsh word.

786
00:56:00,790 --> 00:56:02,382
To be brutally honest...

787
00:56:02,559 --> 00:56:04,754
...your last album bombed.

788
00:56:04,928 --> 00:56:08,728
Your tours, they can't even fill a club.
While his-

789
00:56:09,299 --> 00:56:11,290
His filled stadiums.

790
00:56:12,268 --> 00:56:16,967
You haven't had a number one single in,
what, 18 years?

791
00:56:17,574 --> 00:56:20,702
You know, I mean, do you honestly think
you can make this happen?

792
00:56:21,511 --> 00:56:24,810
I can make the sun rise in the west.

793
00:56:28,918 --> 00:56:30,283
So...

794
00:56:32,555 --> 00:56:33,579
...what do you say?

795
00:56:35,892 --> 00:56:37,359
You know what?

796
00:56:38,461 --> 00:56:40,088
Get to work.

797
00:56:41,364 --> 00:56:42,831
Good choice.

798
00:56:49,272 --> 00:56:54,835
Yes, I told him to use his dead son's song
to promote his career.

799
00:56:55,011 --> 00:56:58,811
- And no, I don't have any guilt about that.
- So you're not stealing?

800
00:56:59,249 --> 00:57:02,912
I am giving Trevor Evans
his wildest dream.

801
00:57:03,086 --> 00:57:05,486
Are you telling me
his son wouldn't want that?

802
00:57:06,122 --> 00:57:10,422
- You're not being honest with me.
- I am the most honest person you know.

803
00:57:11,561 --> 00:57:14,257
I am the only person
who is willing to admit...

804
00:57:14,764 --> 00:57:17,460
...what the rest of the world never will.

805
00:57:17,967 --> 00:57:19,696
I'm in this for me.

806
00:57:19,869 --> 00:57:22,463
But at what cost?

807
00:57:24,841 --> 00:57:27,366
What goes around
does not come around.

808
00:57:27,544 --> 00:57:28,841
Believe me.

809
00:57:29,012 --> 00:57:30,639
If it did...

810
00:57:30,980 --> 00:57:34,006
...my father would not
have made billions.

811
00:57:34,184 --> 00:57:36,345
X:
You just don't know.

812
00:57:37,821 --> 00:57:40,221
If you were anywhere on the planet
six months ago...

813
00:57:40,390 --> 00:57:43,518
...then you heard all about Will Evans'
death on the 10 freeway...

814
00:57:43,693 --> 00:57:47,629
...just after his first big tour date.
Just an amazingly sad story.

815
00:57:47,797 --> 00:57:51,528
Well, tonight, Will's father,
rock legend Trevor Evans, is here...

816
00:57:51,701 --> 00:57:55,364
...to talk about and debut
his brand-new single, "On and On. "

817
00:57:55,538 --> 00:57:57,870
He's dedicated it to his son Will.

818
00:57:58,041 --> 00:57:59,941
I've heard it. It's amazing.

819
00:58:00,109 --> 00:58:02,270
So, everybody,
let's bring out Trevor Evans.

820
00:58:02,445 --> 00:58:03,571
MAN:
Yeah!

821
00:58:03,746 --> 00:58:05,737
[CROWD CHEERING]

822
00:58:05,949 --> 00:58:07,940
[PLAYING "ON AND ON"]

823
00:58:20,296 --> 00:58:25,427
[SINGING]
These people try to get inside

824
00:58:25,602 --> 00:58:28,435
My head

825
00:58:31,808 --> 00:58:33,935
Sometimes I think

826
00:58:34,110 --> 00:58:39,912
They'd rather see me dead

827
00:58:45,054 --> 00:58:51,857
Should I get up and walk away

828
00:58:55,331 --> 00:59:02,328
A failure is not what I set out to be

829
00:59:07,310 --> 00:59:12,942
On and on
On and on

830
00:59:13,116 --> 00:59:18,213
On and on

831
00:59:19,956 --> 00:59:22,322
It's the little things

832
00:59:22,492 --> 00:59:28,192
That get me through the day

833
00:59:35,672 --> 00:59:37,401
LANCE:
Selani.

834
00:59:38,308 --> 00:59:40,970
Hey, it's Lancey. He made it.

835
00:59:41,144 --> 00:59:43,442
I thought you got lost in the traffic.
About time.

836
00:59:43,613 --> 00:59:45,672
Come on, baby, move.
I gotta talk business.

837
00:59:45,848 --> 00:59:47,713
Come on, come on.

838
00:59:48,151 --> 00:59:50,881
Come on. Oh, before you go,
come here for a second.

839
00:59:51,054 --> 00:59:52,749
Just bend down for a second.

840
00:59:52,922 --> 00:59:54,389
Okay, go ahead.

841
00:59:54,557 --> 00:59:57,390
- What's up?
- I got your text. Tell me the good news.

842
00:59:57,727 --> 00:59:59,490
- Do you want some sunscreen?
- I'm good.

843
00:59:59,662 --> 01:00:01,425
- Are you sure?
- Selani.

844
01:00:01,898 --> 01:00:03,525
Hold your horses. We got a hearing.

845
01:00:03,700 --> 01:00:06,794
- That's what I wanna hear.
- I know that's what you wanna hear.

846
01:00:07,770 --> 01:00:08,964
[SIGHS]

847
01:00:09,439 --> 01:00:10,804
It's locked down.

848
01:00:10,974 --> 01:00:14,967
- DA's office has to do an investigation, we-
- You couldn't tell me this over the phone?

849
01:00:15,144 --> 01:00:17,009
Over the phone?

850
01:00:17,780 --> 01:00:19,247
WOMAN: Here you go.
- Thank you, baby.

851
01:00:19,415 --> 01:00:22,441
Appreciate that. Go away, we got
business we're trying to finish up here.

852
01:00:22,619 --> 01:00:24,610
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

853
01:00:25,722 --> 01:00:27,189
Right.

854
01:00:31,227 --> 01:00:35,721
Look, these hearings can be touchy.
It's all about controlling the risks.

855
01:00:39,469 --> 01:00:41,437
Now, listen to me a second.

856
01:00:41,838 --> 01:00:45,365
Angelica's oncologist was a guy
by the name of Spenser Hamilton, okay?

857
01:00:45,541 --> 01:00:47,372
His testimony is gonna be critical...

858
01:00:47,543 --> 01:00:50,603
...to your sister's state of mind
at the time of her disappearance.

859
01:00:50,780 --> 01:00:52,304
So if, uh...

860
01:00:53,449 --> 01:00:56,213
If he testifies that she's...

861
01:00:56,386 --> 01:00:59,287
...say, suicidal?

862
01:01:07,563 --> 01:01:09,326
Well, now...

863
01:01:11,000 --> 01:01:12,900
...that would make a difference, yeah.

864
01:01:13,302 --> 01:01:14,667
Yeah.

865
01:01:14,837 --> 01:01:16,270
Yeah.

866
01:01:18,107 --> 01:01:20,405
This has been very helpful.

867
01:01:20,910 --> 01:01:23,902
I'm glad, Lance.
I'm glad it's been helpful.

868
01:01:26,516 --> 01:01:27,710
Let's get a drink.

869
01:01:27,884 --> 01:01:29,784
Yo, baby.

870
01:01:29,952 --> 01:01:32,887
Hey, we need another drink over here.

871
01:01:33,089 --> 01:01:35,216
She's all upset now. Baby, I'm sorry.

872
01:01:35,391 --> 01:01:37,450
I'm sorry. Please come back.

873
01:01:37,794 --> 01:01:39,125
[CAR ALARM CHIRPS]

874
01:01:47,336 --> 01:01:51,067
LANCE: It's never easy to escape our past,
doctor.

875
01:01:51,607 --> 01:01:53,199
The truth is...

876
01:01:53,376 --> 01:01:55,276
...we are all on the run.

877
01:01:55,511 --> 01:02:00,107
But today is the day
when it has all caught up to you.

878
01:02:01,017 --> 01:02:02,041
Right now.

879
01:02:03,319 --> 01:02:08,086
Right now you're feeling that electric sting
running down your spine.

880
01:02:08,391 --> 01:02:11,258
The shock, the regret.

881
01:02:12,095 --> 01:02:14,029
"How does he know?

882
01:02:14,464 --> 01:02:16,295
What should I do?"

883
01:02:17,934 --> 01:02:19,959
None of that matters now.

884
01:02:20,703 --> 01:02:24,867
All that matters now is whether
you want everyone you've ever met...

885
01:02:25,041 --> 01:02:28,340
...to learn that you fathered a child
with one of your patients...

886
01:02:28,511 --> 01:02:30,604
...only to abandon them.

887
01:02:31,414 --> 01:02:35,646
Or let that secret stay a secret forever.

888
01:02:35,818 --> 01:02:38,378
- What do you want me to do?
LANCE: Testify.

889
01:02:38,755 --> 01:02:39,949
SPENSER:
What?

890
01:02:40,123 --> 01:02:42,489
LANCE:
My sister wanted to die.

891
01:02:43,593 --> 01:02:45,026
Why do you care?

892
01:02:45,194 --> 01:02:49,221
You've got far bigger problems than that,
don't you, doctor?

893
01:02:52,568 --> 01:02:54,593
See you in court.

894
01:02:59,442 --> 01:03:01,740
JAKE:
It doesn't matter what he said.

895
01:03:01,911 --> 01:03:04,436
It doesn't matter what he offered you.

896
01:03:04,847 --> 01:03:07,680
Perjury is a crime.

897
01:03:07,917 --> 01:03:10,283
And you will be prosecuted.

898
01:03:25,234 --> 01:03:26,826
He got to the doctor.

899
01:03:27,303 --> 01:03:28,463
How do you know?

900
01:03:28,638 --> 01:03:31,004
You should've seen his face.

901
01:03:31,908 --> 01:03:33,637
Whatever they got on him, it's good.

902
01:03:34,343 --> 01:03:35,776
So, what's the doctor's story?

903
01:03:35,945 --> 01:03:39,142
He says that Vita was depressed
from the terminal cancer.

904
01:03:39,315 --> 01:03:42,148
Likely went to an exotic destination
and committed suicide...

905
01:03:42,318 --> 01:03:44,183
...or died of the cancer in private.

906
01:03:44,854 --> 01:03:47,584
- What if he's telling the truth?
- He's not.

907
01:03:47,757 --> 01:03:49,850
Are you willing to bet your career
on that?

908
01:03:50,026 --> 01:03:51,618
She's in Mexico.

909
01:03:51,794 --> 01:03:53,591
You know it and I know it.

910
01:03:53,763 --> 01:03:56,493
And she did it to herself.

911
01:03:56,666 --> 01:03:59,726
And we're never gonna be able
to do anything about that.

912
01:04:00,136 --> 01:04:03,936
You coerced a man
into lying under oath.

913
01:04:04,106 --> 01:04:08,099
I convinced a liar to tell more lies.

914
01:04:10,012 --> 01:04:11,673
Hello, Lance.

915
01:04:12,381 --> 01:04:13,780
The detective is no liar.

916
01:04:13,950 --> 01:04:17,317
Detective Russell lacks...

917
01:04:17,620 --> 01:04:18,985
...perspective.

918
01:04:24,460 --> 01:04:26,724
One million dollars.

919
01:04:32,768 --> 01:04:36,465
It'll attract too much attention
all at once.

920
01:04:36,672 --> 01:04:39,232
But after a couple of years...

921
01:04:39,408 --> 01:04:41,467
...you'll get everything.

922
01:04:47,783 --> 01:04:49,216
I don't want your money.

923
01:04:50,019 --> 01:04:53,750
Come on. That's rash.

924
01:04:54,423 --> 01:04:57,984
Who will get the money
if it doesn't go to me?

925
01:04:59,195 --> 01:05:00,890
No one.

926
01:05:02,398 --> 01:05:03,956
Is that what you want?

927
01:05:04,901 --> 01:05:08,837
Losing a wife,
that changed you, didn't it?

928
01:05:09,005 --> 01:05:11,872
Because something has to make sense,
doesn't it?

929
01:05:12,041 --> 01:05:15,442
It can't be so random
that someone like me has everything...

930
01:05:15,611 --> 01:05:19,775
...while someone like you
has to suffer so much.

931
01:05:19,949 --> 01:05:23,715
Something has to balance it out,
doesn't it?

932
01:05:25,354 --> 01:05:27,083
Justice.

933
01:05:28,691 --> 01:05:30,716
Right, detective?

934
01:05:33,996 --> 01:05:37,659
Feels good to make this about her,
doesn't it?

935
01:05:39,035 --> 01:05:41,367
This is about her.

936
01:05:44,440 --> 01:05:45,464
It's about you.

937
01:05:46,042 --> 01:05:48,237
I'm not the one who's dead.

938
01:05:48,844 --> 01:05:50,471
No.

939
01:05:50,646 --> 01:05:52,910
But if you keep this up...

940
01:05:53,115 --> 01:05:54,343
...you will be.

941
01:05:54,984 --> 01:05:57,714
Do you know my father cut me out
of his will?

942
01:05:59,121 --> 01:06:00,986
He was abusive...

943
01:06:01,157 --> 01:06:02,556
...my father...

944
01:06:03,492 --> 01:06:06,052
...in just about every way possible.

945
01:06:08,264 --> 01:06:12,166
I decided enough was enough.
Angelica didn't.

946
01:06:13,402 --> 01:06:15,233
I'm not a shrink.

947
01:06:18,474 --> 01:06:19,736
Ever remarry?

948
01:06:22,044 --> 01:06:23,443
No.

949
01:06:28,384 --> 01:06:30,511
One million dollars.

950
01:06:32,221 --> 01:06:34,189
I get my money.

951
01:06:35,324 --> 01:06:37,519
And you get a new life.

952
01:06:37,827 --> 01:06:39,158
[BILLIARD BALLS CLATTER]

953
01:06:39,328 --> 01:06:41,762
How'd you know about my wife?

954
01:07:08,257 --> 01:07:10,054
I can't stop thinking about her.

955
01:07:11,861 --> 01:07:14,159
The painting she was working on...

956
01:07:14,330 --> 01:07:16,195
...I never took it down.

957
01:07:16,866 --> 01:07:22,168
Her clothes are still in the closet,
exactly where she left them.

958
01:07:23,939 --> 01:07:26,373
She's still there.

959
01:07:26,876 --> 01:07:29,868
She's still there.

960
01:07:32,815 --> 01:07:34,282
No.

961
01:07:35,117 --> 01:07:36,948
She's gone.

962
01:07:37,953 --> 01:07:40,114
The problem is...

963
01:07:42,224 --> 01:07:44,089
...so are you.

964
01:07:47,596 --> 01:07:49,120
God help me.

965
01:07:54,870 --> 01:07:56,963
TREVOR: Thanks, pal.
- Have fun.

966
01:07:57,139 --> 01:07:59,107
TREVOR:
To the new tour.

967
01:07:59,275 --> 01:08:01,300
["ON AND ON" PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

968
01:08:01,844 --> 01:08:04,005
Been a long time.

969
01:08:06,515 --> 01:08:08,415
Too long.

970
01:08:10,519 --> 01:08:12,544
Taking these with you?

971
01:08:14,256 --> 01:08:16,281
I'm good.

972
01:08:17,693 --> 01:08:19,627
Is that so?

973
01:08:21,430 --> 01:08:23,295
So tell me...

974
01:08:24,834 --> 01:08:27,462
...late at night when you're all alone...

975
01:08:27,636 --> 01:08:32,471
...in that big hotel suite...

976
01:08:33,676 --> 01:08:39,478
...and the adrenaline of the cheers
from the crowds have long subsided...

977
01:08:40,049 --> 01:08:43,576
...and all you are left with
are the haunting sounds...

978
01:08:43,752 --> 01:08:46,744
...of your son singing...

979
01:08:47,089 --> 01:08:49,080
..."On and On"...

980
01:08:52,261 --> 01:08:54,024
...what then?

981
01:09:00,636 --> 01:09:02,194
X:
Truth is like water.

982
01:09:02,371 --> 01:09:08,401
It washes away the dirt and the filth
of lies and deception.

983
01:09:08,944 --> 01:09:11,742
But we can't live on water alone.

984
01:09:12,148 --> 01:09:15,879
Peace is what sustains us
like a warm meal.

985
01:09:17,419 --> 01:09:19,649
JAKE:
Everett was in on it.

986
01:09:20,623 --> 01:09:22,682
X:
You have been lied to...

987
01:09:22,858 --> 01:09:25,383
...and you have been deceived.

988
01:09:26,095 --> 01:09:28,689
The truth will wash that away.

989
01:09:28,864 --> 01:09:31,799
But, Jake, you must find peace...

990
01:09:31,967 --> 01:09:34,128
...and in that absolution...

991
01:09:35,104 --> 01:09:37,334
...you will be healed.

992
01:09:43,112 --> 01:09:44,739
EVERETT:
You've got 90 seconds.

993
01:09:48,784 --> 01:09:53,016
That's a bit dramatic, don't you think?
You could ask for a transfer.

994
01:09:53,189 --> 01:09:55,089
Why didn't you tell me?

995
01:09:55,257 --> 01:10:00,092
Because you have yet to understand
the difference between what is legal...

996
01:10:00,262 --> 01:10:01,854
...and what is justice.

997
01:10:03,332 --> 01:10:04,663
This is not justice.

998
01:10:05,000 --> 01:10:07,833
Really? For Lance, it was.

999
01:10:08,003 --> 01:10:11,063
He got what he should have been given
a long time ago.

1000
01:10:12,341 --> 01:10:14,809
It was a good deal he offered you.

1001
01:10:14,977 --> 01:10:16,308
You should have taken it.

1002
01:10:17,079 --> 01:10:19,104
You tipped off Ortus.

1003
01:10:19,281 --> 01:10:21,044
Then you tipped off Lance.

1004
01:10:21,217 --> 01:10:24,653
Then you undermined my testimony
after I left, didn't you?

1005
01:10:29,592 --> 01:10:32,527
What about you? What did you want?

1006
01:10:34,129 --> 01:10:36,029
Absolution.

1007
01:10:37,066 --> 01:10:38,397
[DOOR SLAMS]

1008
01:10:41,704 --> 01:10:46,232
I see that the party wants to nominate you
for the DA's office.

1009
01:10:46,642 --> 01:10:49,042
Congratulations.

1010
01:10:49,945 --> 01:10:51,606
Thank you.

1011
01:10:57,253 --> 01:11:01,087
What does Alice think about all of this?

1012
01:11:16,005 --> 01:11:17,905
I don't know.

1013
01:11:19,475 --> 01:11:21,272
I see.

1014
01:11:22,945 --> 01:11:24,913
And why is that?

1015
01:11:35,190 --> 01:11:37,090
It's complicated.

1016
01:11:57,212 --> 01:12:02,445
LANCE:
Today I made $1.78 billion.

1017
01:12:02,618 --> 01:12:04,745
Billion with a B.

1018
01:12:08,157 --> 01:12:10,352
X:
And how do you feel?

1019
01:12:12,828 --> 01:12:15,058
LANCE:
I don't feel anything.

1020
01:12:16,231 --> 01:12:19,200
X:
And you wonder why you're not happy.

1021
01:12:19,668 --> 01:12:22,796
When a stone falls into a pond...

1022
01:12:23,772 --> 01:12:26,002
...it's not one act.

1023
01:12:26,742 --> 01:12:29,734
It's the beginning of a thousand ripples.

1024
01:12:30,813 --> 01:12:32,144
One simple act...

1025
01:12:33,682 --> 01:12:37,584
...creating a wave
that can drown this entire city.

